h3. Issue Summary

Using the smart value {{{{issueType}}}} or {{{{issueType.name}}}} does not work on [Lookup issues|https://support.atlassian.com/jira-software-cloud/docs/automation-actions/#Automationactions-Lookupissues]
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Setup an automation rule
 # Add an action to lookup issues
 # Add an action to log the lookup results and use {{issueType}} smart value.

Log action :
{code:java}
{{#lookupIssues}} 
{{url}} : {{issueType}}
{{/}}
{code}
h3. Expected Results

The issue type of the results should be logged.
h3. Actual Results

The issue type column will be blank
h3. Workaround

Use the the following notation inside lookupissue to display the issue type in the results. Text in lowercase returns results.

{{{\{issuetype.name}}}}

h3. Problem Definition

We don't support cascading selects yet.

h3. Workaround

Workaround from https://support.atlassian.com/jira-software-cloud/docs/advanced-field-editing-json/#field-syntax-examples:
{code}
{
   "fields": {
  "First Field" : { "value": "First value", "child": { "value" : "Child value"} }
    }
}
{code}

h3. Issue Summary

When using Jira REST API to get the issue remote links, the response does not contain Confluence page titles. It shows only "Wiki page".
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Link JIRA and Confluence using app links
 # Link a JIRA issue with a Confluence page by clicking on "Link Confluence page"
 # Get remote issue links using the REST API:
{code:java}
'https://your-domain.atlassian.com/rest/api/3/issue/{issueIdOrKey}/remotelink'{code}

h3. Expected Results

The response should contain the Page title linked to the issue.
h3. Actual Results

Only page URL is shown. The page title is displayed as "*Wiki Page*" or "*Page*" as per the below example:
{code:java}
[
  {
    "relationship": "Wiki Page",
    "object": {
      "url": "https://your-domain.atlassian.net/wiki/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=xxxxxxxx",
      "title": "Wiki Page",
      "icon": {},
      "status": {
        "icon": {}
      }
    }
  }
]
{code}
h3. Workaround

Currently, there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
